	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To all the paladins that think you cant effectively heal during combat you are wrong. You can heal during combat, but its only really effective if you are taking only one mob on if multiple ones are hitting you its more difficult because of the timing issue.<BR>
<BR>
1. Leave AutoAttack on and keep whacking away.<BR>
<BR>
2. As soon as the mob hits you or misses hit tab, cast your spell and tab back to the mob before your spell finishes casting.<BR>
<BR>
3. Continue attacking the enemy.<BR>
<BR>
You dont need to wait for the spell to fully cast before you can keep attacking the enemy. Hopefully if you spell doesnt fizzle you well finish your spell while you continue to attack.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
