			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				When used properly light healing can increase your chances for survival during battle.  It will also allow you to target stronger monsters for melee.  Immediately following your opponents swing, hit F1, then hit the spell hotkey.  As soon as your casting time is met then reselect your target and you will swing.  There is no need to shut off auto attack (don't worry, you wont attack yourself).  I can sucessfully heal myself thoughout the entire battle with no delay on 2hs, and only a slight delay on 1hs or 1hb.  This method also works with cure poison when fighting venemous spiders such as crags.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
